               <floruit notBefore="1300" notAfter="1399">He was a monk of 14th century who came from <placeName ref="LOC1310Aksum">ʾAksum</placeName>
                  to the monastery called <placeName ref="LOC6457Zazo">Zāzo</placeName>. <persName ref="PRS8041Qozmos">Qozmos</persName> 
                  was an extreme ascetic who lived in a separate cell and refused all cooked food, as well as the Eucharist. 
                  He was highly accepted by those who practiced  the religion of Jews in <placeName ref="LOC5671Semen">Semen</placeName> 
                  and <placeName ref="LOC5498Sallam">Ṣallamt</placeName> who viewed him as a semi-divine. </floruit>
                  
